And I left my autograph book at home.

1176
01:47:45,000 --> 01:47:46,718
His Eminence called me.

1177
01:47:46,877 --> 01:47:48,094
He wants to see you.

1178
01:47:48,587 --> 01:47:50,305
Probably wants to fire me himself.

1179
01:47:51,423 --> 01:47:53,767
He wants to give you the Intelligence Star.

1180
01:47:54,969 --> 01:47:56,812
You're getting the highest award of merit...

1181
01:47:57,012 --> 01:48:00,357
of the Clandestine Services
of these United States.

1182
01:48:01,308 --> 01:48:03,231
Ceremony's on the 14th.

1183
01:48:03,394 --> 01:48:06,568
If they push it a week, I can bring Ian.
That's his winter break.

1184
01:48:08,065 --> 01:48:12,411
The op was classified,
so the ceremony's classified.

1185
01:48:12,569 --> 01:48:15,618
He can't know about it.
Nobody can know about it.

1186
01:48:17,157 --> 01:48:20,252
So they're just gonna give me an award
and then they're gonna take it back.

1187
01:48:20,828 --> 01:48:21,875
That's right.

1188
01:48:23,747 --> 01:48:26,091
If we wanted applause,
we would've joined the circus.

1189
01:48:27,793 --> 01:48:29,021
I thought we did.

1190
01:48:30,587 --> 01:48:33,386
Carter said you were a great American.

1191
01:48:34,091 --> 01:48:35,764
Great American what?

1192
01:48:36,301 --> 01:48:37,769
He didn't say.

1193
01:48:51,108 --> 01:48:52,360
What happened to your picture?

1194
01:48:53,986 --> 01:48:55,203
It's in turnaround.

1195
01:49:37,488 --> 01:49:39,081
Can I come in?

1196
01:50:25,077 --> 01:50:30,017
<i>The Iran Hostage Crisis ended on January 20, 1981,
when all remaining hostages were released.</i>

1197
01:50:30,947 --> 01:50:35,878
<i>They spent 444 days in captivity.</i>

1198
01:50:37,422 --> 01:50:42,802
<i>The involvement of the C.I.A. complemented efforts
of the Canadian embassy in freeing the six held in Tehran.</i>

1199
01:50:43,330 --> 01:50:47,556
<i>To this day, this story stands as an enduring model
for international cooperation between governments.</i>

1200
01:50:48,976 --> 01:50:55,404
<i>All of the Houseguests returned to the
U.S. Foreign Service after their ordeal in Iran.</i>

1201
01:50:56,942 --> 01:51:03,072
<i>Oscar-winning makeup artist John Chambers was awarded
the C.I.A.'s Intelligence Medal, its highest civilian honor.</i>

1202
01:51:03,198 --> 01:51:06,920
<i>He and Mendez remained friends
until Chambers' death in 2001.</i>

1203
01:51:08,704 --> 01:51:15,679
<i>Tony Mendez's Intelligence Star was returned to him in 1997,
when the Argo operation was declassified by President Clinton.</i>

1204
01:51:25,721 --> 01:51:33,697
<i>He lives in rural Maryland with his family.</i>

1205
01:53:26,133 --> 01:53:31,139
<i>They went in, as you know,
under the guise of creating a motion-picture film.</i>

1206
01:53:31,346 --> 01:53:35,977
<i>But that it had a very high possibility of failure.</i>

1207
01:53:36,143 --> 01:53:38,441
<i>And after it was successful, of course...</i>

1208
01:53:38,603 --> 01:53:41,402
<i>it was a great temptation
to reveal all the stories...</i>

1209
01:53:41,565 --> 01:53:44,990
<i>so maybe I could take a little bit
of credit for it, since I was president...</i>

1210
01:53:45,152 --> 01:53:49,749
<i>but we had to keep it secret.
Tony Mendez has gone down in CIA history...</i>

1211
01:53:49,906 --> 01:53:51,783
<i>after his retirement...</i>

1212
01:53:51,950 --> 01:53:58,799
<i>as one of the 50 most important
CIA operatives of all time.</i>

1213
01:53:59,416 --> 01:54:04,798
<i>Eventually we got every hostage
back home, safe and sound...</i>

1214
01:54:04,963 --> 01:54:08,968
